According to my understanding and how Darwinism is playing out,I think this will happen in the next 6 months.

The final model you will talk to  will come out like a mixture of these architectures

1. Modular networks
2. MOE core Architecture
3. Plug-in Network
4. Federated Learning

Now it’s the early stage what I call the egg stage, New subnets are emerging with multiple use cases each with distinct features. In maybe a month the first Subnet will be deregistered.

With such high incentives, Bittensor will attract the best talent in Building and developing the best models.

Let’s say we have a really good Image model, Finance model, Prediction model, Multiple expert Text generation models. We will build a base inference model where you you can ask questions.

Let’s say you want to know how your investment on Brazilian sugar would be in 6 months. 

First the inference model will understand the request and ask the Research subnet for a all the Datapoints and how best we can predict the price of Brazilian sugar from all knowledge available. Let’s say it says check the past data then it will ping the finance subnet to get the past data. And then if it’s need to know user sentiment it will ask the api subnet to check twitter, Reddit etc to get the current data and send that to the sentiment analysis subnet to understand the situation after that it may be sent to the prediction model to get the data back the base model will then understand everything and give the final answer. 

We can also have human subnets where users are rewarded for real life activities like going to event and buying a merch or OpenAI a bank account😎

This is my prediction and anything can happen.

There is an other possibility where we train models on the subnets data and update them like in a federation architecture.

In response to the issues with registering new keys. Miners on SN18 work hard to get the required rate limits and key access and if they perform as they should servicing the network, then they will not be kicked off.

However any deviation from 10% performance will leave them open to being replaced. Mass key reg is not a path to success, which we feel levels the landscape to all.
